            <title>[GROOVY-2156] Parameter annotations cannot be queried at runtime</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2156</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This problem occurs with the Groovy-1.1-beta-3-SNAPSHOT that comes with Grails 0.6. When I use reflection to query the parameter annotations of a class&apos;s method, a call to &apos;value()&apos; on any of those annotations causes a java.lang.annotation.IncompleteAnnotationException. Note that this does not happen with annotations declared on a method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached zip file contains a library and a Groovy script. Simply run the script with the library in the classpath and you should see the error (unless it&apos;s been fixed already &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; ).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
